  "description": "The bird was mostly calm and content to perch and preen. \u00a0It only moved when attacked by a Red-tailed Hawk, which happened a couple of times.\u00a0\r\nIt had an orange beak with a light blue tip, dark capped and crested head, white on the neck and also the lower portion of the front of the body. \u00a0It was dark in the middle and it had horizontal barring at the bottom portion of the white neck. \u00a0When it flew it had the white outer wing tips and white tail with the dark band.\r\nIt didn't vocalize that I could tell.",
